<div class="splash-container three-quarter" id='home'>
  <div class="d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center">
    <div class='main-header-wrapper p-5'>
      <h1 class="main-header alfa-slab">
        Third party javascript tags <br/>
        <span class='strikethrough'>are</span><span class='replace-text'>used to be</span><br/>
        your #1 blindspot.
      </h1>
      <h2 class="sub-header">
        Third party tags inherently make your web application more vulnerable due to loss of visibility, control, and stability. 
        Tagsafe provides a set of tools to put you back in control of your site.
      </h2>
      <% if Util.env_is_true('DOMAIN_AUDIT_FORM_ENABLED') %>
        <div class='container mt-5'>
          <div class='col-xs-12 col-md-6 offset-md-3'>
            <%= form_with url: domain_audits_path, class: 'domain-audit-form', data: { controller: 'loading_form' } do |f| %>
              <div class='inline-input-and-btn'>
                <%= f.text_field :domain_url, placeholder: 'https://www.tagsafe.io', value: @domain_audit_url, class: 'form-control' %>
                <%= loading_submit_button 'Measure Impact of Third Party Tags' %>
              </div>
            <% end %>
            <% if @domain_audit_error %>
              <span class='red-text d-block'><%= @domain_audit_error %></span>
            <% end %>
            <span class='domain-audit-explanation'>Enter your site's URL to measure the impact of your third party tags.</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      <% else %>
        <div class='mt-5'>
          <%= link_to 'Get started', new_registration_path, class: 'tagsafe-btn outline rounded-corners large d-block m-auto' %>
          <span>No credit card required.</span>
        </div>
      <% end %>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="splash-container fit-content why-tagsafe-container text-start" id='why'>
  <div class="container-fluid">
    <div class="row align-items-center">
      <div class="col-xs-12 col-md-6">
        <h2 class="alfa-slab mb-3">What's the problem with using tags?</h2>
        <p class="sub-header">
          Third party tags are a vital piece to modern web applications, however the processes around them are completely broken. With each tag added to your site
          you provide other developers the ability to freely push changes to your site without your knowledge. 
        </p>
        <p class="sub-header">
          Tagsafe is here to instill the processes we maticulously follow for first party releases. After all, you wouldn't allow your own developers to push 
          to production whenever they please, why do we allow our tag providers to do so?
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class='col-xs-12 col-md-6'>
        <img src="<%= asset_cdn_url('/pipes.png') %>" class="img-fluid">
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

